qas.question: Who was Unicode developed in conjunction with?

What includes topics like bitwise encoding, collation, and rendering?

What is another name for Unicode?

context: <b6_0>Unicode<b6_0/> is developed in conjunction with the <a0_0><b4_0>International Organization for Standardization<b4_0/><a0_0/> and shares the character repertoire with <b5_0>ISO/IEC 10646<b5_0/>: <a1_0>the Universal Character Set<a1_0/>. <b8_0>Unicode and ISO/IEC 10646<b8_0/> function equivalently as character encodings, but <a2_0>The Unicode Standard<a2_0/> contains much more information for <b7_0>implementers<b7_0/>, covering—in depth—topics such as bitwise encoding, collation and rendering. The Unicode Standard enumerates a multitude of character properties, including those needed for supporting bidirectional text. The two standards do use <a3_0>slightly different terminology<a3_0/>.
